title: "Out of Africa Have I Called My Son."
description: Photograph of African troops marching behind a white officer.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen

title: Spahis (Negroid Algerians) at Salonica
description: Photograph of Spahis, one of many light cavalrymen in the French army, from the French colonies in North Africa: Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen

title: Voice of Congo: "If your uncle would have left us our hands, Albert, we could be of more use to you now!"
creator.name: Charleston, E. A.
description: Political cartoon depicting Prince Albert of Belgium meeting with a Congolese man from the Belgian Congo colony.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen

title: Daudi Chua, King of Uganda, with His Regents
description: Photograph of King Chua, two regents, and four Englishmen in official British garb.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen

title: Europe's Wedges and Wars in Africa
description: Map depicting "wedges of civilization" representing Great Britain, France, Portugal, Germany, Italy, and Spain and their scramble to control parts of Africa.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen

title: A Lesson in Philanthropy-Nit.
creator.name: McGowan, Foster
description: Political cartoon depicting King Leopold chewing on a bone with one side covered in rubber while a British officer stands by frothing at the mouth, begging for the leavings.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen

title: Three Sentries at Lokongia with Prisoner
description: Photograph of three sentries with a prisoner in Lokongia, Congo.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen

title: Mutilated Congo Natives--A Few Survivor
description: Collage of photographs of Congolese men and women mutilated by Belgian forces.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen

title: Number Five--Belgian Civilization in Africa
description: Political cartoon depicting King Leopold sitting on his throne decorated with human skulls and bones.
contributor.name: Jones, Jeannette Eileen
